Product Requirement Document (PRD)
Project: Grama Voice: A Digital Grievance Redressal Portal for Village Welfare
Tagline: “Raising Village Voices, Digitally.”
1. Objective

The goal of Grama Voice is to provide a transparent, accessible, and efficient digital platform for villagers to report local issues (e.g., street lights, sanitation, water leaks), track progress, and receive responses from their Panchayat. The system ensures real-time grievance redressal while promoting accountability and good governance.

2. Key Stakeholders

Citizens (Users): Report and track grievances.

Panchayat Admins: Manage complaints and provide updates.

Super Admin (Govt/NGO/Authority): Manage all Panchayats, monitor overall system performance, and ensure accountability.

3. User Roles & Permissions
Citizen (User)

Register/Login using phone number + OTP.

Submit grievances (with title, description, photo, location).

Track issue status in real time.

View history of submitted issues.

Earn achievement badges (e.g., “Active Citizen”).

Panchayat Admin

Login with username/password.

View complaints assigned to their Panchayat.

Update complaint status: Pending → In Progress → Resolved.

Upload response notes/photos.

View analytics of their Panchayat performance.

Super Admin

Manage all Panchayats (add/remove admins, assign villages).

Manage users (block/unblock if necessary).

Monitor all complaints across villages.

View analytics dashboard: total complaints, solved %, average resolution time.

Generate reports for governance.

4. Core Features
Authentication

OTP-based login for citizens (custom PHP OTP system).

Secure login for Panchayat Admins & Super Admin.

Complaint Management

Citizens submit complaints with photos & geolocation.

Status updates visible to citizens in real time.

Panchayat Admin updates and resolves complaints.

Tracking & Transparency

Status timeline (Pending → In Progress → Resolved).

Citizens notified of status updates.

Public “Recently Resolved” issues displayed on landing page.

Landing Page

Hero section with CTA ("Report an Issue").

Display achievements (Issues Solved, Panchayats Connected, Satisfaction %).

Showcase recently solved issues (carousel).

Process explanation: Report → Review → Action → Resolved.

Testimonials from citizens & Panchayats.

Footer with quick links & contact info.

Achievements System

Badges for Panchayats (e.g., Fastest Resolution).

Badges for citizens (e.g., Active Reporter).

Achievements displayed on dashboard & landing page.

Super Admin Dashboard

Overview Metrics: Total users, total complaints, resolution rate, avg time.

Complaint Heatmap: Visual map of hotspots.

Leaderboards: Panchayats ranked by performance.

CRUD Operations: Manage Panchayat Admins & Users.

